Create or update flow canvas draft, returns flow UUID (flowUuid). If validation fails, returns structured validation details including valid/errors/warnings/nodeResults. 
Recommended workflow for AI caller: first call query_flow_node_config_schema to get type-specific config schema, then call save_flow. 
Input object: req (FlowSaveReqDTO). 
Mode selection (important): 
- create: do NOT pass flowUuid and parentFlowUuid; 
- new_version: pass parentFlowUuid (base version flowUuid), do NOT pass flowUuid. If versionType is omitted, MCP defaults it to 3 (new version); 
- update_draft: pass flowUuid (draft flowUuid to update), do NOT pass parentFlowUuid. If the draft already exists, MCP will reuse its saved versionType when versionType is omitted. 
Common required fields: projectId, flowName, nodeList, edgeList. 
Graph constraints: 
- each node.id must be unique in nodeList; 
- edge.source and edge.target must refer to existing node.id; 
- edgeList must form a directed acyclic graph (DAG); do not create cycles. 
- flow should include exactly one entry node and at least one exit_flow node; 
- each exit_flow node must have exactly one incoming edge and no outgoing edges; 
- sourceBranchId is only needed for branch/judge node outgoing edges. 
For push node channelId fields (such as message_push, webhook_push, wechat_push), call query_channel_list first and use a valid channelId from that tool. 
For time-unit related enum fields, always pass lowercase enum values such as day/hour/minute/week/month; do not pass uppercase values like DAY or MINUTE. 
config fields: node.config and edge.config are JSON strings (not JSON objects). 
Minimal create example: 
{"req":{"projectId":1,"flowName":"Welcome Flow","nodeList":[{"id":"node_1","type":"single_trigger","config":"{}"},{"id":"node_2","type":"exit_flow","config":"{}"}],"edgeList":[{"source":"node_1","target":"node_2"}]}}.

